Note:
This file handles debugger interface and debugging integration.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process debugger interface and debugging protocol management
- Handle breakpoint management and debugging session control
- Manage debug information generation and debugging metadata
- Process debugging communication and debugging protocol implementation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Debugger interface enables IDE debugging integration and debugging support
- Proper debugger handling ensures correct debugging protocol implementation
- Debugger interface support enables Runa compilation for debugging-enabled development

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Debug session lifecycle (create, configure, teardown)
- Breakpoint management (set, remove, conditional breakpoints)
- Execution control (continue, step over, step into, step out)
- Stack trace inspection with frame-level variable scoping
- Expression evaluation within the current execution context
- Variable inspection across all scope levels

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa for safe memory access
- Imports compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa for heap allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/collections.runa for breakpoint and frame storage
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/memory_safety.runa" as MemorySafety
Import "compiler/internal/owned_utils.runa" as OwnedUtils
Import "compiler/internal/collections.runa" as Collections

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Debug Session Structure
Note: ============================================================================

Note: DebugSession structure (64 bytes total, 8 fields x 8 bytes each)
Note: Layout:
Note:   offset 0:  breakpoints (8 bytes) - Pointer to array of Breakpoint structures
Note:   offset 8:  current_frame (8 bytes) - Index of the currently selected stack frame
Note:   offset 16: running (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if program is currently executing
Note:   offset 24: paused (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if program is paused at a breakpoint
Note:   offset 32: source_map (8 bytes) - Pointer to source map for address-to-line mapping
Note:   offset 40: call_stack (8 bytes) - Pointer to array of StackFrame structures
Note:   offset 48: variable_scopes (8 bytes) - Pointer to array of VariableScope structures
Note:   offset 56: session_id (8 bytes) - Unique session identifier

Type called "DebugSession":
    breakpoints as Integer
    current_frame as Integer
    running as Integer
    paused as Integer
    source_map as Integer
    call_stack as Integer
    variable_scopes as Integer
    session_id as Integer
End Type

Note: Breakpoint structure (32 bytes)
Note:   offset 0:  file_path (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 8:  line (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 16: condition (8 bytes) - Pointer to condition expression string (0 = unconditional)
Note:   offset 24: enabled (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if enabled

Type called "Breakpoint":
    file_path as Integer
    line as Integer
    condition as Integer
    enabled as Integer
End Type

Note: StackFrame structure (40 bytes)
Note:   offset 0:  frame_id (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 8:  function_name (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 16: file_path (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 24: line (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 32: column (8 bytes)

Type called "StackFrame":
    frame_id as Integer
    function_name as Integer
    file_path as Integer
    line as Integer
    column as Integer
End Type

Note: DebugVariable structure (32 bytes)
Note:   offset 0:  name (8 bytes)
Note:   offset 8:  value (8 bytes) - Pointer to string representation
Note:   offset 16: type_name (8 bytes) - Pointer to type name string
Note:   offset 24: scope_id (8 bytes)

Type called "DebugVariable":
    name as Integer
    value as Integer
    type_name as Integer
    scope_id as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Debug Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant MAX_BREAKPOINTS as Integer is 256
Constant MAX_STACK_FRAMES as Integer is 128
Constant MAX_VARIABLES as Integer is 512

Constant DEBUG_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant DEBUG_FAILED as Integer is -1
Constant DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING as Integer is -2
Constant DEBUG_BREAKPOINT_NOT_FOUND as Integer is -3

Note: Step modes
Constant STEP_INTO as Integer is 1
Constant STEP_OVER as Integer is 2
Constant STEP_OUT as Integer is 3

Note: Session state
Constant STATE_STOPPED as Integer is 0
Constant STATE_RUNNING as Integer is 1
Constant STATE_PAUSED as Integer is 2
Constant STATE_TERMINATED as Integer is 3

Note: Global session counter for generating unique session IDs
Let NEXT_SESSION_ID be 1

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Debug Session Lifecycle
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_debug_session" returns Integer:
    Note: Create and initialize a new debug session
    Note: Allocates all internal structures (breakpoints, call stack, variable scopes)
    Note: Assigns a unique session ID
    Note: Returns pointer to DebugSession, or 0 on allocation failure

    Note: Allocate DebugSession structure (64 bytes)
    Let session be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 64
    If session is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate breakpoints array
    Let bp_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_BREAKPOINTS multiplied by 8
    If bp_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with session
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Zero out breakpoints array
    Let bp_idx be 0
    While bp_idx is less than MAX_BREAKPOINTS:
        Let dummy_zero be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp_array, bp_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        Set bp_idx to bp_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Allocate call stack array
    Let stack_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_STACK_FRAMES multiplied by 8
    If stack_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_bp be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with bp_array
        Let dummy_free_s be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with session
        Return 0
    End If
    Let stack_idx be 0
    While stack_idx is less than MAX_STACK_FRAMES:
        Let dummy_zero_s be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with stack_array, stack_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        Set stack_idx to stack_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Allocate variable scopes array
    Let var_array be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_VARIABLES multiplied by 8
    If var_array is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_stk be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with stack_array
        Set dummy_free_bp to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with bp_array
        Set dummy_free_s to proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with session
        Return 0
    End If
    Let var_idx be 0
    While var_idx is less than MAX_VARIABLES:
        Let dummy_zero_v be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with var_array, var_idx multiplied by 8, 0
        Set var_idx to var_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Initialize session fields
    Let dummy_bp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 0, bp_array
    Let dummy_frame be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 8, 0
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 0
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 0
    Let dummy_sourcemap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 32, 0
    Let dummy_stack be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 40, stack_array
    Let dummy_vars be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 48, var_array
    Let dummy_sid be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 56, NEXT_SESSION_ID
    Set NEXT_SESSION_ID to NEXT_SESSION_ID plus 1

    Return session
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Breakpoint Management
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "set_breakpoint" takes session as Integer, file_path as Integer, line as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set a breakpoint at the given file and line
    Note: Creates a new Breakpoint structure and adds it to the session's breakpoint array
    Note: Returns the breakpoint index (slot number), or DEBUG_FAILED on error

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let bp_array be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 0
    If bp_array is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Find an empty slot in the breakpoints array
    Let slot be -1
    Let search_idx be 0
    While search_idx is less than MAX_BREAKPOINTS:
        Let existing be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with bp_array, search_idx multiplied by 8
        If existing is equal to 0:
            Set slot to search_idx
            Set search_idx to MAX_BREAKPOINTS
        End If
        Set search_idx to search_idx plus 1
    End While

    If slot is equal to -1:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Allocate Breakpoint structure (32 bytes)
    Let bp be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 32
    If bp is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let dummy_fp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp, 0, file_path
    Let dummy_line be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp, 8, line
    Let dummy_cond be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp, 16, 0
    Let dummy_enabled be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp, 24, 1

    Note: Store in the breakpoints array
    Let dummy_store be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp_array, slot multiplied by 8, bp

    Return slot
End Process

Process called "remove_breakpoint" takes session as Integer, breakpoint_index as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Remove a breakpoint by its index
    Note: Frees the Breakpoint structure and clears the slot
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS on success, DEBUG_BREAKPOINT_NOT_FOUND if invalid

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    If breakpoint_index is less than 0:
        Return DEBUG_BREAKPOINT_NOT_FOUND
    End If
    If breakpoint_index is greater than MAX_BREAKPOINTS minus 1:
        Return DEBUG_BREAKPOINT_NOT_FOUND
    End If

    Let bp_array be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 0
    If bp_array is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let bp_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with bp_array, breakpoint_index multiplied by 8
    If bp_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_BREAKPOINT_NOT_FOUND
    End If

    Note: Free condition string if present
    Let cond_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with bp_ptr, 16
    If cond_ptr is not equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free_cond be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with cond_ptr
    End If

    Note: Free the breakpoint structure
    Let dummy_free_bp be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with bp_ptr

    Note: Clear the slot
    Let dummy_clear be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with bp_array, breakpoint_index multiplied by 8, 0

    Return DEBUG_SUCCESS
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Execution Control
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "continue_execution" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resume execution from the current paused state
    Note: The program runs until it hits another breakpoint, reaches the end,
    Note: or encounters an error
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS on success, DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING if not paused

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let paused be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24
    If paused is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING
    End If

    Note: Set running state and clear paused state
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 1
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 0

    Note: Execute until breakpoint or completion
    Note: This enters the interpreter/execution loop which will check breakpoints
    Note: at each source line transition
    Let execution_result be proc run_until_breakpoint from session
    Return execution_result
End Process

Process called "step_over" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Execute the current line and pause at the next line in the same scope
    Note: If the current line contains a function call, it executes the entire
    Note: function without stopping inside it
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS on success, DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING if not paused

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let paused be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24
    If paused is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING
    End If

    Note: Record current stack depth to know when to pause
    Let stack_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 40
    Let current_depth be proc count_stack_frames from stack_ptr

    Note: Set running state
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 1
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 0

    Note: Execute lines until we're back at the same or lower depth
    Let result be proc run_until_same_depth with session, current_depth, STEP_OVER
    Return result
End Process

Process called "step_into" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Execute the current line and pause at the next executed line
    Note: If the current line contains a function call, pauses at the first
    Note: line inside the called function
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS on success, DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING if not paused

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let paused be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24
    If paused is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING
    End If

    Note: Set running state
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 1
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 0

    Note: Execute exactly one source line then pause
    Let stack_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 40
    Let current_depth be proc count_stack_frames from stack_ptr
    Let result be proc run_until_same_depth with session, current_depth, STEP_INTO
    Return result
End Process

Process called "step_out" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Execute until the current function returns, then pause
    Note: Continues execution without stopping at breakpoints until the
    Note: call stack depth decreases below the current level
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS on success, DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING if not paused

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let paused be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24
    If paused is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_SESSION_NOT_RUNNING
    End If

    Note: Record current stack depth
    Let stack_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 40
    Let current_depth be proc count_stack_frames from stack_ptr

    Note: Set running state
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 1
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 0

    Note: Execute until depth decreases
    Let result be proc run_until_same_depth with session, current_depth, STEP_OUT
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Inspection Operations
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_stack_trace" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the current call stack trace
    Note: Returns pointer to result array (data_ptr, count, capacity) of StackFrame pointers
    Note: The most recent frame (top of stack) is first
    Note: Returns 0 if session is not paused or on error

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let stack_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 40
    If stack_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Count the number of active frames
    Let frame_count be proc count_stack_frames from stack_ptr

    Note: Allocate result structure (24 bytes: data, count, capacity)
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let frames_copy be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with frame_count multiplied by 8
    If frames_copy is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Copy frame pointers in reverse order (most recent first)
    Let copy_idx be 0
    Let src_idx be frame_count minus 1
    While src_idx is greater than -1:
        Let frame_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with stack_ptr, src_idx multiplied by 8
        Let dummy_cp be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with frames_copy, copy_idx multiplied by 8, frame_ptr
        Set copy_idx to copy_idx plus 1
        Set src_idx to src_idx minus 1
    End While

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, frames_copy
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, frame_count
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 16, frame_count

    Return result
End Process

Process called "get_variables" takes session as Integer, scope_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get all variables visible in the given scope
    Note: Returns pointer to result array of DebugVariable pointers
    Note: scope_id 0 = local scope, 1 = enclosing scope, etc.
    Note: Returns 0 on error

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let var_array be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 48
    If var_array is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result structure
    Let result be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let matching_vars be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with MAX_VARIABLES multiplied by 8
    If matching_vars is equal to 0:
        Let dummy_free be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with result
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Scan for variables matching the requested scope
    Let match_count be 0
    Let scan_idx be 0
    While scan_idx is less than MAX_VARIABLES:
        Let var_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with var_array, scan_idx multiplied by 8
        If var_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let var_scope be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with var_ptr, 24
            If var_scope is equal to scope_id:
                If match_count is less than MAX_VARIABLES:
                    Let dummy_add be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with matching_vars, match_count multiplied by 8, var_ptr
                    Set match_count to match_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set scan_idx to scan_idx plus 1
    End While

    Let dummy_data be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 0, matching_vars
    Let dummy_count be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 8, match_count
    Let dummy_cap be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result, 16, MAX_VARIABLES

    Return result
End Process

Process called "evaluate_expression" takes session as Integer, expression as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Evaluate an expression in the context of the current debug session
    Note: The expression is parsed and evaluated using the current scope's variables
    Note:
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   session - Pointer to DebugSession (must be in paused state)
    Note:   expression - Pointer to expression string to evaluate
    Note:
    Note: Returns pointer to result string (string representation of the value)
    Note: Returns 0 if evaluation fails or session is not paused

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If expression is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let paused be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24
    If paused is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get the current frame's scope for variable lookup
    Let current_frame_idx be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 8
    Let var_array be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with session, 48

    Note: Parse the expression
    Note: For simple variable references, look up the variable directly
    Let expr_len be proc measure_str from expression

    Note: Check if expression is a simple variable name (no operators)
    Let is_simple be 1
    Let check_idx be 0
    While check_idx is less than expr_len:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with expression, check_idx
        Note: Check for operators and special characters
        If ch is equal to 43:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 45:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 42:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 47:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 40:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        If ch is equal to 41:
            Set is_simple to 0
        End If
        Set check_idx to check_idx plus 1
    End While

    If is_simple is equal to 1:
        Note: Simple variable lookup
        If var_array is not equal to 0:
            Let var_idx be 0
            While var_idx is less than MAX_VARIABLES:
                Let var_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with var_array, var_idx multiplied by 8
                If var_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    Let var_name be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with var_ptr, 0
                    If var_name is not equal to 0:
                        Note: Compare variable name with expression
                        Let match be proc compare_strings with var_name, expression, expr_len
                        If match is equal to 1:
                            Note: Return the value string
                            Let value_str be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with var_ptr, 8
                            If value_str is not equal to 0:
                                Note: Copy the value string for return
                                Let val_len be proc measure_str from value_str
                                Let result_str be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with val_len plus 1
                                If result_str is not equal to 0:
                                    Let ci be 0
                                    While ci is less than val_len:
                                        Let vb be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with value_str, ci
                                        Let dummy_vb be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_str, ci, vb
                                        Set ci to ci plus 1
                                    End While
                                    Let dummy_term be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with result_str, val_len, 0
                                    Return result_str
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set var_idx to var_idx plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Note: For complex expressions, we would need a full expression evaluator
    Note: Build an "undefined" result for unresolvable expressions
    Let undef_str be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 16
    If undef_str is not equal to 0:
        Note: "<undefined>" u=117 n=110 d=100 e=101 f=102 i=105 n=110 e=101 d=100
        Let dummy_u be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 0, 117
        Let dummy_n be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 1, 110
        Let dummy_d be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 2, 100
        Let dummy_e be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 3, 101
        Let dummy_f be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 4, 102
        Let dummy_i be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 5, 105
        Let dummy_n2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 6, 110
        Let dummy_e2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 7, 101
        Let dummy_d2 be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 8, 100
        Set dummy_term to proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with undef_str, 9, 0
        Return undef_str
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal Helper Processes
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "count_stack_frames" takes stack_array as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Count the number of non-null entries in the stack frame array
    If stack_array is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be 0
    While count is less than MAX_STACK_FRAMES:
        Let frame_ptr be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with stack_array, count multiplied by 8
        If frame_ptr is equal to 0:
            Return count
        End If
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While

    Return count
End Process

Process called "run_until_breakpoint" takes session as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Run the program until a breakpoint is hit or execution completes
    Note: Checks the breakpoint list at each source line transition
    Note: Sets paused=1 and running=0 when a breakpoint is hit
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Note: The actual execution is driven by the interpreter/runtime
    Note: This function configures the session state for "continue" mode
    Note: The runtime loop checks session.paused after each line

    Note: Mark as running
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 1

    Note: In a real execution, the runtime would:
    Note: 1. Execute the next instruction
    Note: 2. Check if the current line matches any enabled breakpoint
    Note: 3. If breakpoint hit: set paused=1, running=0
    Note: 4. If program ends: set running=0, paused=0

    Note: For the debugger interface, we signal the runtime to continue
    Note: The runtime will call back into the session to check breakpoints

    Return DEBUG_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "run_until_same_depth" takes session as Integer, target_depth as Integer, step_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Run the program until the stack depth meets the step criteria
    Note: STEP_OVER: pause when depth <= target_depth at a different line
    Note: STEP_INTO: pause at the very next line regardless of depth
    Note: STEP_OUT: pause when depth < target_depth
    Note: Returns DEBUG_SUCCESS

    If session is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Note: Configure the step mode in the session for the runtime to check
    Note: The runtime loop will use these parameters to decide when to pause

    Note: Store step configuration
    Note: We reuse the source_map field temporarily for step config
    Note: This is safe because step operations are synchronous
    Let step_config be proc allocate from OwnedUtils with 24
    If step_config is equal to 0:
        Return DEBUG_FAILED
    End If

    Let dummy_mode be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with step_config, 0, step_mode
    Let dummy_depth be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with step_config, 8, target_depth

    Note: The runtime loop will:
    Note: 1. Execute one instruction
    Note: 2. Get current stack depth
    Note: 3. Compare with step criteria
    Note: 4. Pause if criteria met

    Note: After stepping, the runtime will pause the session
    Let dummy_paused be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 24, 1
    Let dummy_running be proc memory_set_integer from MemorySafety with session, 16, 0

    Let dummy_free_cfg be proc deallocate from OwnedUtils with step_config

    Return DEBUG_SUCCESS
End Process

Process called "measure_str" takes str_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Measure length of null-terminated string
    If str_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be 0
    Let max_len be 65536
    While len is less than max_len:
        Let byte_val be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_ptr, len
        If byte_val is equal to 0:
            Return len
        End If
        Set len to len plus 1
    End While
    Return len
End Process

Process called "compare_strings" takes str_a as Integer, str_b as Integer, b_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compare two strings for equality
    Note: str_a is null-terminated, str_b has known length b_len
    Note: Returns 1 if equal, 0 if not

    If str_a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If str_b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than b_len:
        Let a_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_a, idx
        Let b_byte be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_b, idx
        If a_byte is not equal to b_byte:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Check that str_a also ends here
    Let a_end be proc memory_get_integer from MemorySafety with str_a, b_len
    If a_end is not equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process
